# Drive AR Direct Clear input inactive and load the '0' output
output-drive='---1111-1010L11111---111111111111111'

# LOAD TEST the CARRY OUTPUT.

# output-drives-strength defines how much current the outputs can sink.
# This is a value is what the tester will load the output with.
output-drive-strength='18mA'

# Those two values will define the voltage drop over the transistor compared to ground. First
# the nominal value and then a margin that defines how much the value could diff from that.
output-voltage-high='-150mV'
output-voltage-margin='100mV'


####################################################################################
#
# Making an adapter for testing pins BA & BB
#
# The R210 has no spare signals.
# Pins DA & DB are signals rather than power supplies
#
# The following instructions allow you to build an interposing board between the
# brs-tester and connector board. See photo in the Drawings directory.
#
# Build details:
#
# Taking a spare connector PCB, fit the JP1,2,3,4 connectors. Leave the edge
# connectors unfitted, we will used those to jumper signals.
#
# Modify the connector board:
# 1. Cut track from JP3 (on the -> Tester side) to BA2
# 2. Cut track from JP3 (on the -> Tester side) to BB2
# 3. Jumper BA2 to AF2
# 4. Jumper BB2 to AP2
#
# This has the effect of
# - Connecting the level input on the DCD gate driving the FF clear to ~Q
# - Connecting the level input on the DCD gate driving the FF set to Q
# - Converting BJ input into a complement signal
#
# Failure to toggle indicates a fault in one of the two DCD gates.
#
#
#             CCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDD
#             ABCDEFHJKLMNPRSTUVABCDEFHJKLMNPRSTUV
#             pppooooi--iiiiiiiipppiiiiiooiiiiiiii
#                  |      |     ||
#                  |      \______/
#                  |            |
#                  \____________/
#
#
####################################################################################
